verses.text:
I will become like a lion to the people of Ephraim in Israel;
\q2 I will become like a young lion to the people of Judah. 
\q1 I will destroy them and leave them;
\q1 I will carry them far away,
\q2 and no one will be able to rescue them.
\q1

Then I will go back to where I came from; 
\q2 from there I will wait for them to admit that they have sinned; 
\q1 I will wait for them to come and ask me to help them."

Gilead is a city of people who do wicked things;
\q2 in the streets of that city are the footprints of murderers.
\q1

They are all sexually immoral;
\q2 they burn with lust like a baker's oven that is burning hot;
\q1 once he lights the fire, he does not need to put any more wood on it, 
\q1 until he is ready to bake the bread. 
\q1

The people of Ephraim have built many altars on which to offer sacrifices for their sins;
\q2 however, these altars have become places where the people commit terrible sins against me. 
\q1

No longer will they pour out wine to offer it to Yahweh;
\q2 their sacrifices will not please him at all.
\q2 Their sacrifices will be as unacceptable to God as the food that people eat at funerals;
\q1 and everyone who eats that food becomes unacceptable to God.
\q1 That food will be all they eat;
\q2 they will not be able to bring it into Yahweh's house to offer it to him.
\q1

The people of Israel have caused Yahweh to become very angry;
\q2 their Lord says that they are guilty of the death of many, and that their guilt remains on them. 
\q2 He will pay them back because they have insulted him with their shameful deeds.

So I will attack you like a lion;
\q2 I will attack you like a leopard that waits beside the road to suddenly jump on a traveler.
\q1
